Hello Mark and Team,

a user of our implementation of PHPExcel pointed out this to me.
In OLERead.php on line 304ff (as per PHPExcel 1.8.0) there is the following comment:

// FIX: represent numbers correctly on 64-bit system
// http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1487372&group_id=99160&atid=623334
// Hacked by Andreas Rehm 2006 to ensure correct result of the <<24 block on 32 and 64bit systems

The last line of this comment causes him a "Hacked" warning in his Joomla implementation. I agree with him, that this comment should be "rephrased" or removed.
Kind regards
Ruediger Schultz
Schultz IT Solutions
